2.5 Robustness to Time Bound Exponent

Lemma A.2 (Robustness of Time Bound). Theorem A.1 holds for any polynomial time bound $T(m) = m^k$ with $k \ge 3$, with the minimum handshake length $n$ adjusted as $n \ge N(k)$.

Proof sketch: The Lucas–Lehmer runtime for $M_{p_n}$ scales as $p_n^3 \sim n^3 \log^3 n$. The handshake length $|w^{(n)}| \sim n^2 \log n$. For any $k \ge 3$, we have $n^3 \log^3 n = o((n^2 \log n)^k)$ as $n \to \infty$, so there exists $N(k)$ such that the runtime $t \le |w^{(n)}|^k$ for all $n \ge N(k)$. The program length remains $O(\log n)$, and the gap $\Delta(n)$ grows as $\Omega(n^2 \log n)$. Thus the separation holds for any $k \ge 3$. ∎

