4.2 Photon Budget and SNR

For a direct‑detection PPM receiver, the channel capacity in the presence of background noise is given by:

C \approx \frac{1}{M T_s} \left[ \log_2 M + \eta \bar{n}_s \log_2 \eta \bar{n}_s - (1 + \eta \bar{n}_s) \log_2 (1 + \eta \bar{n}_s) \right]

where $\bar{n}_s$ is mean signal photons per slot, $\eta$ is detector quantum efficiency, and $M$ is PPM order. The SCPPM code is designed to approach this capacity even when $\bar{n}_s < 1$ (the photon‑starved regime).

